{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/theturnpipeline"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"What happens between the player pressing Return and the next prompt.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every line the player types runs through the same fixed sequence of stages. This section walks that sequence — which rules fire, in what order, and how one rule can stop the rest — from raw input to committed state."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"From-input-to-command","text":"From input to command"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/REPL","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" reads a line and hands it to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/perform(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". The parser first turns the text into a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" — an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent"},{"text":" (the canonical action, like ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/take","isActive":true},{"text":") plus the objects, preposition, and direction it resolved.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Parsing can fail: an unknown word, nothing in scope, a verb with no object. ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Parse failures are free.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" No rules run, the state is untouched, and the turn counter does not advance — the player just sees a message (“I don’t understand that.” \/ “You can’t see any such thing here.”) and a fresh prompt. Only a successfully parsed command enters the pipeline below.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"How the parser converses","type":"heading","anchor":"How-the-parser-converses"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Three parser behaviors go beyond one-line-in, one-command-out:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Questions stay open."}]},{"type":"text","text":" When the parser asks a clarifying question — “Which do you mean: the brass lantern or the rusty lantern?”, “What do you want to take?” — the next input line is first tried as its "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"answer"}]},{"type":"text","text":": an adjective ("},{"code":"brass","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), a fuller phrase, or the missing object completes the original command. Narrowing can take several rounds; a line that isn’t an answer simply runs as a fresh command and the question is forgotten. Questions, like all parse failures, are free turns."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pronouns."}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"it","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" refers to the last direct object the player named (naming binds even if the action was refused); ","type":"text"},{"code":"them","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" refers to the group of the last multi-object command. A pronoun whose referent is gone from view fails in scope like any other noun."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-object commands."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"all","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (or ","type":"text"},{"code":"everything","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") in the direct-object slot of "},{"code":"take","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"drop"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"put … in","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"code":"put … on","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" expands to the eligible objects — for ","type":"text"},{"code":"take","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", everything visible, takable, and not already held; for the rest, everything held. Each object then runs stages 1–7 of the pipeline below as its own single-object ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" with a labeled result line ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"brass lantern: Taken."},{"type":"text","text":"), so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rules never see “all”. The each-turn stages (8–9) still run "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"once","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" for the whole command — a burning lantern loses one turn of fuel, not one per object. Other verbs refuse multiple objects, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"all","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" never fills an indirect slot."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"The-stages-of-a-turn","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The stages of a turn"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once a command parses, the engine runs these stages in order. Rules are matched by "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"scope","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (world, the current location, or one of the command’s objects) and by "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"intent"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (a rule with no intents listed matches any)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"World ","type":"text"},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/before(_:perform:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" rules, matching the intent."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Location "},{"code":"beforeEachTurn","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/beforeEachTurn(perform:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the current room, every turn regardless of intent."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Location ","type":"text"},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/before(_:perform:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the current room."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Item ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"}]},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/before(_:perform:)"},{"text":" for the indirect object, then the direct object.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The default action","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — the engine’s built-in behavior for the intent (pick up the item, walk through the exit, describe the thing). This is where the turn actually ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"does"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" something if no rule intervened.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Item "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"}]},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/after(_:perform:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" for the direct object, then the indirect object.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Location "},{"code":"after","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/after(_:perform:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" for the current room.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Location "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"afterEachTurn"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/afterEachTurn(perform:)"},{"type":"text","text":" for the room, every turn."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"World ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"}]},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/after(_:perform:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" rules.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then the turn counter advances by one and the turn commits."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The symmetry is deliberate: "},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" rules run outside-in (world, then location, then item) so broad rules get first say; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rules run inside-out. A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rule is your chance to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"change or forbid","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" what is about to happen; an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rule reacts to what "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"did","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" happen."}]},{"anchor":"Stopping-the-turn-refuse-reply-and-end","level":2,"text":"Stopping the turn: refuse, reply, and end","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A rule body is ordinary Swift, but three helpers change the flow of the turn by throwing an interrupt the engine catches:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/refuse(_:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" — “no, you can’t.” Prints the message and skips the default action and every remaining "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rule. Use it in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rule to veto an action."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/reply(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — “here’s what happens instead.” Mechanically identical to ","type":"text"},{"code":"refuse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but named for the case where you are ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"handling","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the action yourself rather than forbidding it. This is how a custom verb produces its result.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/end(won:)"},{"type":"text","text":" — ends the game, won or lost. The engine prints the final score after the turn’s output."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three return "},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", so they read naturally in a "},{"code":"guard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["cloak.before(.drop, .putOn) {","    guard player.location == cloakroom else {","        try refuse(\"This isn't the best place to leave a smart cloak lying around.\")","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add output "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"without","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" stopping the turn, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/say(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":". It appends a line to the turn’s output and returns normally, so the default action still runs. A "},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" rule that only "},{"code":"say","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s adds flavor; one that "},{"code":"refuse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s or "},{"code":"reply","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s takes over."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"World time passes even on a refusal","anchor":"World-time-passes-even-on-a-refusal","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is one important asymmetry. When a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rule refuses an action, the default action and later "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"text":" rules are skipped — but the turn is still a turn. The each-turn tail (stages 8 and 9) still runs, and the move counter still advances.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is what makes timed puzzles work. A lantern burning down, a guard on patrol, or — in Cloak of Darkness — the darkness that penalizes "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"any"}]},{"type":"text","text":" fumbling in the dark bar, all live in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"afterEachTurn"},{"type":"text","text":" rules, and they tick even on the turns the player wasted trying something forbidden. Each-turn rules run independently: if one throws, the engine catches it and moves on to the next, so one region’s daemon can’t silently kill another’s."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Meta intents skip everything","anchor":"Meta-intents-skip-everything","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A few intents talk to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"game program"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", not the game world: "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/score"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/quit"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/version","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". These are "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"meta","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" intents. They run no rules at all and do not consume a turn — asking for your score is not an action the world should react to, and it should not advance a timed puzzle. Everything in the numbered list above is gated on the intent not being meta."}]},{"text":"Everything commits at once","anchor":"Everything-commits-at-once","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Throughout the turn, rules and the default action read and write a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"scratch"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" copy of the world state. Nothing is visible outside the turn until it finishes. At the very end, the engine commits that scratch state in one step and returns a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TurnResult","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — the text to print, whether the game is now finished, and the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StatusLine","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to show."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Because all mutation funnels through one committed value, a turn is atomic: the player never observes a half-applied turn, and (in a later release) saving the game is just serializing that value. This is the same single-state design described in ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"title":"The Turn Pipeline"},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","type":"topic","title":"Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location/after(_:perform:)":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location\/after(_:perform:)","title":"after(_:perform:)","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/after(_:perform:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"after","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Intent","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"},{"kind":"text","text":"..., "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"perform"},{"kind":"text","text":": () "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV","text":"Rule"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Runs after the default action when the named intents succeed in this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"location.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent/quit":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"quit","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV","text":"Intent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Quit the game."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/quit","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/intent\/quit","kind":"symbol","title":"quit","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GettingStarted":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build and run your first text adventure, one piece at a time."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gettingstarted","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","title":"Getting Started with Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/AddingCustomVerbs":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Teach the parser words the built-in table doesn’t know.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/addingcustomverbs","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","title":"Adding Custom Verbs"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/StatusLine":{"title":"StatusLine","abstract":[{"text":"The status line a handler can display: location, score, and turn count.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StatusLine"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StatusLine"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/statusline","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StatusLine","kind":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/refuse(_:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"refuse(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/refuse(_:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"refuse"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5NeverO","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Never"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/refuse(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"Blocks the current action with a complaint. The default action and any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remaining ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"text":" rules are skipped; world time still passes.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/World/before(_:perform:)":{"title":"before(_:perform:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/before(_:perform:)","abstract":[{"text":"Runs before the default action whenever the named intents are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"attempted, anywhere.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/world\/before(_:perform:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"before","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"},{"text":"..., ","kind":"text"},{"text":"perform","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": () ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rule","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location/before(_:perform:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"before(_:perform:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/before(_:perform:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"before","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV","text":"Intent"},{"kind":"text","text":"..., "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"perform"},{"text":": () ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV","text":"Rule","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location\/before(_:perform:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs before the default action when the named intents are attempted"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in this location."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent/version":{"role":"symbol","title":"version","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/version","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"sta